{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Place buckwheat into mixing bowl and mill <nobr>1 min\/speed 9<\/nobr>. Transfer into a bowl and set aside.","Place sugar into mixing bowl and mill <nobr>1 min\/speed 9<\/nobr>.","Add butter and chop <nobr>10 sec\/speed 6<\/nobr>."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>.  Mix <nobr>50 sec\/speed 3.5<\/nobr>, or until light and fluffy."," <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Crack egg into a small bowl. Mix <nobr>30 sec\/speed 4<\/nobr>, adding egg slowly through hole in mixing bowl lid. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add all remaining ingredients, including reserved buckwheat, and mix <nobr>15 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>, until combined. Transfer into a bowl and place into refrigerator for 30 minutes.","Preheat oven to 180°C . Line two baking trays (30 x 40 cm) with baking paper and set aside.","Roll 1 tablespoon of cookie dough into a ball and place onto prepared tray, flattening slightly with the back of a spoon. Repeat with remaining dough to make approx. 20 balls, placing balls approx. 2 cm apart onto trays. Bake for 12-15 minutes (180°C), or until golden brown. Leave to cool slighty on trays, then transfer onto a wire rack to cool completely. Serve immediately or place into a sealable container until ready to serve."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["150 g buckwheat","130 g raw sugar","110 g unsalted butter, softened","1 egg","½ tsp bicarbonate of soda","½ tsp salt","100 g white chocolate chips","1 tsp vanilla bean paste","1 tsp ground cardamom"]}],"id":"r112636","imageLink":"https:\/\/1.bp.blogspot.com\/-ZtbbKl_wiog\/XZWqqTBXwUI\/AAAAAAAAfbY\/BEgvs0o-QDshMb2byx57zbpUF7R1qAGzQCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_RpLYzudaJocVttQM.png","title":"White chocolate and cardamom buckwheat cookies","publishedAt":"2016-11-20T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"1.7 g","fat":"6.6 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"14.3 g","calories":"512 kJ \/ 122 kcal"},"usefulItems":"bowl, small bowl , baking tray (30 x 40 cm), baking paper, wire rack, sealable container, refrigerator, oven","basicInfo":["easy","10m","55m","20 pieces"]}